====Usage notes====
The term "surname" may be used to translate terms from non-English names which carry additional shades of meaning, most notably in the case of Roman [[cognomen]]s. In fact, the ''[[nomen]]'' was the surname as the word is commonly understood today but the terms were first applied when surname was still used in the sense of "additional" or "added" name: the cognomen was added to the nomen to show the branch of the family involved. (The modern translation of a similar distinction in ancient Chinese names customarily uses [[ancestral name]] and [[clan]] name instead and typically speaks of surnames only once the two merged into a single and commonly-employed family name.)

